				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\hbox {MoS}_2$$\end{document} is commonly seen at the interface between Mo and the kesterite, and the electrical properties of MoS2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
